    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skconstraint"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object describes a mathematical constraint on a node’s position or orientation. Constraints are attached to nodes; after a scene processes any actions and physics interactions, it applies constraints attached to nodes in its node tree. Use constraints to ensure that certain relationships are true before a scene is rendered. For example, you might use a constraint to:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Change a node’s "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sknode/1483089-zrotation"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " property so that it always points at another node or a position in the scene."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Keep a node within a specified distance of another node or a point in the scene."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Keep a node inside a specified rectangle."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Restrict the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sknode/1483089-zrotation"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " property of a node so that it has a more limited rotation range of motion."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To use constraints, create an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsarray"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object that contains one or more constraint objects and assign the array to a node’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sknode/1483124-constraints"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. When the scene is evaluated, the constraints on a node are executed in the order they appear in the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/sknode/1483124-constraints"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " array."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Once created, a constraint can’t be changed. However, you can selectively disable or enable a constraint by setting its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skconstraint/1519669-enabled"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. You can also use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skconstraint/1520369-referencenode"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to convert positions to the referenced coordinate system before applying the constraint."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
